SUMMARY:Kicking It at Hermann Park
DTSTAMP:20260618T144416Z
DTSTART:20260612T000000Z
DESCRIPTION:This summer\, Hermann Park Conservancy will welcome the world t
	o Houston with Kicking It at Hermann Park\, presented by ExxonMobil—a free
	\, public celebration of culture\, community\, and the unifying spirit of 
	sport. Featuring a dynamic mix of programming\, diverse food offerings\, l
	ive entertainment\, and family-friendly activities\, everything will take 
	place in the Commons\, the vibrant 26-acre play and gathering space in the
	 southwest corner of the Park. \n\n📍 The Commons at Hermann Park\n📅 Weeken
	d and select weekdays from June 12 – July 5\n🎟️ Free & open to the public\n
	\nKicking It at Hermann Park will run on weekends and select weekdays from
	 Friday\, June 12\, through Sunday\, July 5\, offering 15 days of engaging
	 experiences for Houstonians and visitors alike during a globally signific
	ant moment for the city. \nThe roster of dynamic programming will include:
	 \n\n🎶 Live music & entertainment\n🍴 Local food trucks & culinary offering
	s\n🎬 Outdoor movie nights\n⚽ Soccer-inspired play & interactive experience
	s\n🌿 Nature-based activities\n👨‍👩‍👧 Family-friendly programming\n🎭 Cultural ce
	lebrations highlighting Houston’s diversity\n\nThank you to ExxonMobil for
	 their generous support! \n \n+++ \nDATES & THEMES\nStay tuned for more de
	tails and a complete programming calendar. Activities are subject to chang
	e and more may be added. Visit the Conservancy tent on-site in the Commons
	 for any questions!\n \nWEEKEND ONE (JUNE 12 – JUNE 14) PDF SCHEDULE HERE.
	 \nWEEKEND TWO (JUNE 19 – JUNE 21) PDF SCHEDULE HERE. \nFriday\, June 12 (
	5 – 9 p.m.): Kickoff in the Park \n\n5 – 6 PM: Trees for Texas: A Backyard
	 Tree Walk (Astros Foundation Pavilion – The Commons)\n5 – 7 PM: Carousel 
	Karaoke (Lott Family Carousel – The Commons)\n6 – 7 PM: Seeds for Success:
	 The Art of Starting a Garden (Cullen Pavilion – The Commons)\n7 – 8 PM: P
	erennials in the Park: Garden Discovery Tour (Astros Foundation Pavilion –
	 The Commons)\n7 – 9 PM: Open Decks: Live DJ Experience (Powell Foundation
	 Terrace – between Water Play Area and Space Adventure in the Commons)\n\n
	Saturday\, June 13 (3 – 10 p.m.): Texas Heritage \n\n3 PM: “One Wan”: Japa
	nese Garden Tea Ceremony (Japanese Garden)\n3 – 4 PM: T is for Texas! Twan
	da’s Theatre on Wheels from Young Audiences of Houston (Tsuru Family Terra
	ce – The Commons)\n3 – 4 PM: Hidden Invaders: Understanding Invasive Speci
	es (Next to Lott Family Carousel – The Commons)\n4 – 5 PM: Rhythms of Trad
	ition: Mixteco Ballet Folklorico from Young Audiences of Houston (Tsuru Fa
	mily Terrace – The Commons)\n4 – 5 PM: Winding Paths of the Japanese Garde
	n: Guided Tour (Japanese Garden)\n5 PM: “One Wan”: Japanese Garden Tea Cer
	emony (Japanese Garden)\n5 -6 PM: Perennials in the Park Tour (McGovern Ce
	ntennial Gardens)\n5 – 8 PM: Hooked on Fishing! Youth Fishing with 4-H (Fi
	shing Pier – The Commons)\n5 – 8 PM: DJ Areal: Music in the Commons (Tsuru
	 Family Terrace – The Commons)\n6 – 7 PM: A Walk Through Tranquility: Japa
	nese Garden Tour (Japanese Garden)\n8:30 PM: Moonlight Movie Nights presen
	ted by Goya: The Parent Trap (Doreen Stoller Lawn – The Commons)\n\nSunday
	\, June 14 (3 – 9 p.m.): Family & Global Community Day \n\n3 PM: “One Wan”
	: Japanese Garden Tea Ceremony (Japanese Garden)\n4 – 5 PM: A Walk Through
	 Tranquility: Japanese Garden Tour (Japanese Garden)\n5 PM: “One Wan”: Jap
	anese Garden Tea Ceremony (Japanese Garden)\n5 – 6 PM: Mosaic Workshop fro
	m Young Audiences of Houston (Astros Foundation Pavilion – The Commons)\n5
	 – 6 PM: Bats-a-Billion: Discover the World of Bats (Cullen Pavilion – The
	 Commons)\n6 – 7 PM: Winding Paths of the Japanese Garden: Guided Tour (Ja
	panese Garden)\n7 – 9 PM: Jazz in the Park with Bayou City Jazz Band (Tsur
	u Family Terrace – The Commons)\n\nWednesday\, June 17 (3 – 9 p.m.): Welln
	ess in the Park – THIS DATE HAS BEEN CANCELED DUE TO INCLEMENT WEATHER! \n
	Friday\, June 19 (5 – 9 p.m.): Juneteenth Celebration \n\n5 – 6 PM: “Kick 
	Into Creativity” Eco Art Studio (Astros Foundation Pavilion – The Commons)
	\n5 – 6 PM: A Walk Through Tranquility: Japanese Garden Tour (Japanese Gar
	den)\n5 – 7 PM: Carousel Karaoke (Lott Family Carousel – The Commons)\n5 –
	 9 PM: “WildGins” Tasting (Next to the Carousel and Play Areas in the Comm
	ons)\n6 – 7 PM: Voices from the Past: “Git” On Board – The Life of Harriet
	 Tubman from Young Audiences of Houston (Tsuru Family Terrace – The Common
	s)\n6 – 7 PM: Roses in Bloom Tour (McGovern Centennial Gardens)\n6 – 8 PM:
	 Soccer for Success by Houston Parks and Recreation Department (Next to th
	e Carousel and Play Areas in the Commons)\n7 – 9 PM: Open Decks: Live DJ E
	xperience with DJ Hiram (Lott Family Carousel – The Commons)\n\nSaturday\,
	 June 20 (3 – 10 p.m.): Global Rhythms \n\n3 – 4 PM: Trees for Texas: A Ba
	ckyard Tree Walk (Astros Foundation Pavilion – The Commons)\n3 – 4 PM: Son
	idos Sincopados with Jorge Orta from Young Audiences of Houston (Next to t
	he Carousel and Play Areas in the Commons)\n4 – 5 PM: Beast Boogie (Anthon
	y Silva) Dance Demo from Young Audiences of Houston (Next to the Carousel 
	and Play Areas in the Commons)\n4 – 5 PM: A Walk Through Tranquility: Japa
	nese Garden Tour (Japanese Garden)\n4 – 6 PM: “Kick Into Creativity” Eco A
	rt Studio (Astros Foundation Pavilion – The Commons)\n4 – 6 PM: Line Danci
	ng Class by Texas A&M AgriLife (Tsuru Family Terrace – The Commons)\n4 – 6
	 PM: Smoothie Bike by Texas A&M AgriLife (Tsuru Family Terrace – The Commo
	ns)\n5 – 6 PM: Perennials in the Park Tour (McGovern Centennial Gardens)\n
	5 – 8 PM: DJ Hiram: Music in the Commons (Next to the Carousel and Play Ar
	eas in the Commons)\n6 – 8 PM: Soccer for Success by Houston Parks and Rec
	reation Department (Next to the Carousel and Play Areas in the Commons)\n8
	:30 PM: Moonlight Movie Nights presented by Goya: A Bug’s Life (Doreen Sto
	ller Lawn – The Commons)\n3 – 10 PM: Goya Giveaways (Next to the Carousel 
	and Play Areas in the Commons)\n\nSunday\, June 21 (3 – 9 p.m.): Community
	 & Wellness Day \n\n3 – 4 PM: A Walk Through Tranquility: Japanese Garden 
	Tour (Japanese Garden)\n3 – 7 PM: Discovery Carts by The Health Museum (As
	tros Foundation Pavilion – The Commons)\n4 – 5 PM: Zumba with Tiny Fitness
	 (Tsuru Family Terrace – The Commons)\n4 – 5 PM: Kids’ Yoga Class by Brave
	 Little Company from Young Audiences of Houston (Next to the Carousel and 
	Play Areas in the Commons)\n4 -5 PM: Origami in the Japanese Garden (Japan
	ese Garden)\n4 – 8 PM: Kindstation by Be Kind (Cullen Pavilion – The Commo
	ns)\n5 – 6 PM: Wellness Walk with Urban Paths’ Laura Conely (Tsuru Family 
	Terrace – The Commons)\n5 – 6 PM: Roses in Bloom Tour (McGovern Centennial
	 Gardens)\n6 – 7 PM: Pilates in the Park by Revival Pilates (Tsuru Family 
	Terrace – The Commons)\n6 – 8 PM: Soccer for Success by Houston Parks and 
	Recreation Department (Next to the Carousel and Play Areas in the Commons)
	\n7 – 8 PM: Yoga in the Park by Black Swan Yoga (Tsuru Family Terrace – Th
	e Commons)\n8 – 9 PM: Prioritizing Peace: Sound Bath (Tsuru Family Terrace
	 – The Commons)\n\nTuesday\, June 23 (3 – 9 p.m.): Youth + Play + Sustaina
	bility Day \nFriday\, June 26 (5 – 9 p.m.): Latin Night \nSaturday\, June 
	27 (3 – 10 p.m.): Global DJ Night \nSunday\, June 28 (3 – 9 p.m.): Interna
	tional Culture Day \nMonday\, June 29 (3 – 9 p.m.): Arts + Nature Day \nFr
	iday\, July 3 (5 – 10 p.m.): Summer Nights in the Park \nSaturday\, July 4
	 (3 – 7 p.m.): Celebrate America – Houston Style \nSunday\, July 5 (3 – 9 
	p.m.): Closing Celebration \n+++ \nMOONLIGHT MOVIE NIGHTS\nPresented by Go
	ya \n \nAs part of the summer offerings\, enjoy Moonlight Movie Nights\, p
	resented by Goya\, in the Commons! Movies will start at approximately 8:30
	 p.m.\, around sunset. These movies are free and open to the public. \n\nS
	aturday\, June 13: The Parent Trap (1998\; PG)\nSaturday\, June 20: A Bug’
	s Life (1998\; G)\nSaturday\, June 27: Lilo & Stitch (2002\; PG)\nFriday\,
	 July 3: National Treasure (2004\; PG)\n\nBe sure to get to the Commons ea
	rly to snag your spot on the lawn. Guests are welcome to bring blankets or
	 lawn chairs to settle in for the movie. \n+++ \nTo inquire about sponsors
	hip opportunities and ways to get involved\, email community@hermannpark.o
	rg.\n\nhttps://hermannpark.org/event/kicking-it-at-hermann-park/\n\nFrom H
	ermann Park Conservancy
URL:https://hermannpark.org/event/kicking-it-at-hermann-park/
LOCATION:The Commons
